  "text": "The CODEOWNERS infrastructure in grafana/grafana is a comprehensive system for managing code ownership, validation, and coverage tracking. At its core is the `.github/CODEOWNERS` file, which defines GitHub ownership assignments for various files and directories in the repository. The `.github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml` CI workflow automatically validates the CODEOWNERS file on pull requests using the mszostok/codeowners-validator action, checking for files, duplicate patterns, syntax errors, and unowned files.\n\nThe manifest generation system is orchestrated through npm scripts defined in `package.json` (lines 13-17): `codeowners-manifest` invokes the main index.js, `codeowners-manifest:clean` clears the manifest directory, `codeowners-manifest:generate` creates processed JSON files, `codeowners-manifest:metadata` generates cache metadata, and `codeowners-manifest:raw` produces raw audit data.\n\nThe JavaScript-based manifest generation pipeline works as follows:\n\n1. **Raw Audit Generation** (`scripts/codeowners-manifest/raw.js`): The `generateCodeownersRawAudit` function spawns the `github-codeowners` CLI tool to parse the CODEOWNERS file and produce JSONL-formatted audit data at `codeowners-manifest/audit-raw.jsonl`.\n\n2. **Manifest Generation** (`scripts/codeowners-manifest/generate.js`): The `generateCodeownersManifest` function reads the raw audit JSONL file and generates three JSON files: `teams.json` (all codeowners), `teams-by-filename.json` (file-to-owners mapping), and `filenames-by-team.json` (owner-to-files mapping).\n\n3. **Metadata Generation** (`scripts/codeowners-manifest/metadata.js`): The `generateCodeownersMetadata` function creates cache metadata containing SHA-256 hashes of the repository files and CODEOWNERS file to detect changes.\n\n4. **Complete Orchestration** (`scripts/codeowners-manifest/index.js`): The `generateCodeownersManifestComplete` function coordinates the entire pipeline, checking if cached data is still valid before regenerating manifests.\n\n5. **Constants** (`scripts/codeowners-manifest/constants.js`): Defines file paths for all manifest artifacts.\n\nThe Go feature management system (`pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go`) defines a `codeowner` type (line 5) as a type alias for `string` with a comment noting it must match CODEOWNERS format. It then defines 27 constants representing different Grafana teams (lines 7-36), such as `@grafana/grafana-app-platform-squad`, `@grafana/dashboards-squad`, etc., allowing features to be associated with specific team ownership.\n\nTest coverage tracking is integrated through `jest.config.codeowner.js`, which reads the generated `filenames-by-team.json` manifest and filters Jest test runs to cover only files owned by a specific team. The `scripts/test-coverage-by-codeowner.js` script orchestrates per-team coverage reporting, using the `TEAM_NAME` environment variable to specify which team's code to analyze. The `test:coverage:by-codeowner` npm script (line 38 in package.json) ties this together, requiring the manifest to be generated first.\n\nThis infrastructure enables Grafana to maintain clear code ownership, validate ownership assignments in CI, generate team-specific test coverage reports, and integrate ownership information into the feature management system for feature flagging decisions."
}

